[{"location":"api/#API-documentation","page":"API docs","title":"API documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Exported-structures","page":"API docs","title":"Exported structures","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API docs","title":"API docs","text":"CatalogedCollection\nPropertyConfiguration","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#CitableCollection.CatalogedCollection","page":"API docs","title":"CitableCollection.CatalogedCollection","text":"A collection of citable objects.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#CitableCollection.PropertyConfiguration","page":"API docs","title":"CitableCollection.PropertyConfiguration","text":"Configuration data for a single property in a collection.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Exported-functions","page":"API docs","title":"Exported functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API docs","title":"API docs","text":"catalogdf\ncollectiondfs","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#CitableCollection.catalogdf","page":"API docs","title":"CitableCollection.catalogdf","text":"Parse CEX source data into a catalog of CitableCollections.\n\ncatalogdf(cexsrc; delimiter)\n\n\ncexsrc must have at least one citecollections block and one citeproperties block.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#CitableCollection.collectiondfs","page":"API docs","title":"CitableCollection.collectiondfs","text":"Use catalog to parse CEX source data into a Vector of DataFrames.\n\ncollectiondfs(cexsrc, catalogdf)\ncollectiondfs(cexsrc, catalogdf, delim; limitto)\n\n\ncexsrc must have at least one citedata block with data records matching information in catalog.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Internal-functions","page":"API docs","title":"Internal functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API docs","title":"API docs","text":"CitableCollection.blocksagree\nCitableCollection.catalogdata\nCitableCollection.collectionurns\nCitableCollection.propertydata\nCitableCollection.propertyurns\nCitableCollection.propertyconfigs\nCitableCollection.configured_propertynames","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#CitableCollection.blocksagree","page":"API docs","title":"CitableCollection.blocksagree","text":"True if list of URNs from collections block and properties block document the same set of collections.\n\nblocksagree(collurns, propurns)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#CitableCollection.catalogdata","page":"API docs","title":"CitableCollection.catalogdata","text":"From a list of CEX blocks, extract all data lines from one or more citecollections blocks.\n\ncatalogdata(blocklist)\n\n\nIt is a DomainError if blocklist includes no citecollections blocks.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#CitableCollection.collectionurns","page":"API docs","title":"CitableCollection.collectionurns","text":"Extract URNs of collections documented in datalines.\n\ncollectionurns(datalines)\ncollectionurns(datalines, delim)\n\n\ndatalines is a Vector of delimited-string values.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#CitableCollection.propertydata","page":"API docs","title":"CitableCollection.propertydata","text":"From a list of CEX blocks, extract all data lines from one or more citeproperties blocks.\n\npropertydata(blocklist)\n\n\nIt is a DomainError if blocklist includes no citeproperties blocks.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#CitableCollection.propertyurns","page":"API docs","title":"CitableCollection.propertyurns","text":"Extract collection-level URNs of properties documented in datalines.\n\npropertyurns(datalines)\npropertyurns(datalines, delim)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#CitableCollection.propertyconfigs","page":"API docs","title":"CitableCollection.propertyconfigs","text":"Create a DataFrame of PropertyConfigurations  from delimited-text source.\n\npropertyconfigs(datalines)\npropertyconfigs(datalines, delim)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#CitableCollection.configured_propertynames","page":"API docs","title":"CitableCollection.configured_propertynames","text":"Extract list of property names from a DataFrame of PropertyConfiguration objects.\n\nconfigured_propertynames(df)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#CitableCollection","page":"Overview","title":"CitableCollection","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"Work with collections of citable objects.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Quick-example","page":"Overview","title":"Quick example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"Citable objects belong to a cataloged collection.  We normally work with a single catalog with records for one or more collections, plus a set of data for each cataloged collection.  We can use Julia's DataFrame type for the catalog information, and a Vector of DataFrames for one or more data sets.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"While can work with either a catalog or a data set in distinct DataFrames, the CitableCollection module also includes a CollectionLibrary structure that has members for a catalog DataFrame, and a Vector of DataFrame for data sets.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"This page briefly shows:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"how to read a catalog into a DataFrame\nhow to read datasets into a Vector of DataFrames\nhow to read both at once into a CitableLibrary from a single CEX source","category":"page"},{"location":"#A-cataloged-collection","page":"Overview","title":"A cataloged collection","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"A CatalogedCollection records metadata about a single dataset, including the type of data represented by each property of an object.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"We can read data about multiple cataloged collections with the catalogdf function. It creates a DataFrame for a catalog from a CEX source that must include at least one citecollections block and one citeproperties block.  This example builds a DataFrame with the catalog data for a single collection.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"using CitableCollection, DataFrames\ncollectionmetadata = \"\"\"#!citecollections\n\nURN|Description|Labelling property|Ordering property|License\nurn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1:|Images of the Venetus A manuscriptscript|urn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1.caption:||CC-attribution-share-alike\n\n\n#!citeproperties\n\nProperty|Label|Type|Authority list\nurn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1.urn:|Image URN|Cite2Urn|\nurn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1.caption:|Caption|String|\nurn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1.rights:|License for binary image data|String|CC-attribution-share-alike,public domain\n\"\"\"\ncatdf = catalogdf(collectionmetadata)\nnrow(catdf)\n\n# output\n\n1","category":"page"},{"location":"#Collection-data","page":"Overview","title":"Collection data","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"You can read data for one or more cataloged collections from CEX source. The result is a Vector of DataFrames.  This example has data for a single collection.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"datadbcex = \"\"\"#!citedata\n// Images of the Venetus A manuscript:\n\nurn|caption|rights\nurn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1:IMG1r|Folio 1 recto of the Venetus A, photographed in natural light|CC-attribution-share-alike\nurn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1:IMG1v|Folio 1 verso of the Venetus A, photographed in natural light|CC-attribution-share-alike\n\"\"\"\ndatadfs = collectiondfs(datadbcex, catdf)\nlength(datadfs)\n\n# output\n\n1","category":"page"},{"location":"#Load-a-CitableLibrary","page":"Overview","title":"Load a CitableLibrary","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"The collectionlibrary function reads from a CEX source that includes citecatalog, citeproperties, and citedata blocks.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"fullcex = \"\"\"#!citecollections\n\nURN|Description|Labelling property|Ordering property|License\nurn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1:|Images of the Venetus A manuscriptscript|urn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1.caption:||CC-attribution-share-alike\n\n\n#!citeproperties\n\nProperty|Label|Type|Authority list\nurn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1.urn:|Image URN|Cite2Urn|\nurn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1.caption:|Caption|String|\nurn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1.rights:|License for binary image data|String|CC-attribution-share-alike,public domain\n\n#!citedata\n// Images of the Venetus A manuscript:\n\nurn|caption|rights\nurn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1:IMG1r|Folio 1 recto of the Venetus A, photographed in natural light|CC-attribution-share-alike\nurn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.v1:IMG1v|Folio 1 verso of the Venetus A, photographed in natural light|CC-attribution-share-alike\n\"\"\"\ncollectionlib = collectionlibrary(fullcex)\nisa(collectionlib, CollectionLibrary)\n\n# output\n\ntrue","category":"page"}]
